Conceptual answers: 
A： ITT (Intention to trade) is defined as the effect of treatment regardless of whether the unit actually complied, engaged, or used it. In this setting, the platform of A/B test may not deliver to some users or users may not engage in it, but will be all included in the ITT comparison.
B： Because ITT preserves the randomization 
C： When the researchers want to test the actual behavior, we need to justify our assignment as an instrument, for example, assuming the assignment will impact the engagement.





